      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While it's understandable to want to handle the situation yourself, considering your history with anxiety attacks, it might be better to err on the side of caution. Sitting or lying down could worsen the symptoms, and since you're already feeling extremely exhausted, it might be harder to shake off the feelings once you're asleep. Taking a step back and focusing on your breathing, grounding techniques, or a calming activity on your phone might be a good way to temporarily calm down before deciding on your next step.",
